article.headline: Kent State 77, Western Michigan 62
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Jay Youngblood's 13 points led five Kent State players in double figures in the Golden Flashes' 77-62 win over Western Michigan on Tuesday night. Kent State (11-5, 5-0 Mid-American Conference) shot 65 percent in the second half while holding the Broncos to 36 percent to pull away after Western Michigan (4-11, 1-4) took a 36-34 lead into halftime. DeAndre Haynes added 12 points for the Golden Flashes, and Isaac Knight, Nate Gerwig and Armon Gates had 11 apiece. Knight scored 10 points in the second half and Gates had nine. Center Joe Reintz's 18 points and 10 rebounds led the Broncos, who also got 15 points from Brian Snider. Kent State sank 11 of 14 free throws, while Western Michigan hit 15 of 22.
